#: 01.en.txt:3
msgid ""
"1)\n"
"Libre, Community and Decentralised Networks"
msgstr ""

#: 01.en.txt:8
msgid ""
"2a)\n"
"AlterMundi facilitates the birth of new libre and community networks "
"connected to the internet from a perspective of popular empowerment based on "
"appropriation of technology by way of collaboration among peers and the use "
"and development of libre software and hardware.\n"
"The principal objective is to develop a network model for self-provisioning "
"of communication services in digitally-excluded regions.\n"
"Based on the effort and organization of the community, this model offers the "
"opportunity to satisfy a need now considered basic for human development: "
"digital communication."
msgstr ""

#: 01.en.txt:11
msgid ""
"3a)\n"
"Our little piece of the internet"
msgstr ""

#: 01.en.txt:14
msgid ""
"3b)\n"
"\"Currently 52% of people living on Earth do not have internet access.\" *"
msgstr ""

#: 01.en.txt:18
msgid ""
"3c)\n"
"This inequality is deeper in rural areas of Africa, Latin America and the "
"global south, where the low population density and low income generate "
"little incentive for the deployment of commercial network infrastructure. "
"This makes them digitally excluded or neglected areas.\n"
"In most cases, people living in digitally excluded areas also have other "
"difficulties such as insufficient economic resources, employment, education, "
"transportation, electricity, gender equality and access to land and potable "
"water."
msgstr ""

#: 01.en.txt:21
msgid ""
"3d)\n"
"The fundamental role of libre and community networks is to facilitate the "
"construction of low-cost autonomous technological infrastructure for "
"deployment of internet networks. The primary objective is to overcome the "
"barriers imposed by centralization and control of commercial network "
"infrastructure and the content that circulates on that infrastructure."
msgstr ""

#: 01.en.txt:25
msgid ""
"3e)\n"
"*The State of Broadband: Broadband catalyzing sustainable development. "
"September 2017 / \n"
"Broadband Commission for Sustainable Development - ITU â€“ UNESCO"
msgstr ""

#: 01.en.txt:28
msgid ""
"4a)\n"
"The challenge is not only to facilitate internet access, but rather to build "
"our little piece of the internet via libre and community networks governed "
"by the communities themselves, in collaborative and organized ways."
msgstr ""

#: 01.en.txt:31
msgid ""
"4b)\n"
"Internet is a tool to increase transparency and access to information and to "
"facilitate civic engagement in support of social, cultural, economic and "
"political changes that improve the situation of the communities."
msgstr ""

#: 01.en.txt:35
msgid ""
"4c)\n"
"Libre and community networks encourage the consolidation of cooperative "
"community empowerment processes for an \"other world that is possible.\"\n"
"."
msgstr ""

#: 01.en.txt:38
msgid ""
"4d)\n"
"Seen this way, it becomes vital and necessary to think of the internet as a "
"common good (or as a commons)."
msgstr ""

#: 01.en.txt:41
msgid ""
"5a)\n"
"Libre, community and decentralized networks"
msgstr ""

#: 01.en.txt:44
msgid ""
"5b)\n"
"Upon deciding to connect to the internet, we become part of it and we can "
"choose how to participate in that global network of networks."
msgstr ""

#: 01.en.txt:50
msgid ""
"5c)\n"
"An open, neutral and decentralized network is built by the communities "
"through agreements and consensus. This process collaborates with autonomy, "
"sustainability and the functioning of the libre community network.\n"
"At the same time, it empowers the communities to design the structure and "
"functioning of their own network, respecting local identities and needs.\n"
"Libre community networks allow learning and knowing how the network "
"functions to be able to make decision about the network and not be "
"subordinate to the rules of commerce or the imposed criteria that, in most "
"cases, are opposed to the communities' interests.\n"
"The use and understanding of technologies promotes an inclusive and "
"conscious access to digital resources, facilitating education, learning, "
"sharing knowledge, creating local means of communition and media, civic "
"engagement and social and regional economy."
msgstr ""

