#: 01.en.txt:73
msgid ""
"7a)\n"
"Community networks have specific charateristics that define them and are "
"their strengths:"
msgstr ""

#: 01.en.txt:83
msgid ""
"7b)\n"
"Collective property\n"
"This means that the infrastructure (antennas, routers, cables, etc.) is "
"property of all the member sof the network and of the community that deploys "
"it. There are no individual owners, nor private owners, nor any more "
"important than the others.\n"
"Social management\n"
"Means the network is adminstered by the members of the network. There is no "
"one person that rules, rather the decisions are made by everyone.\n"
"Accessible design\n"
"The infrormation about how the network and its components function is public "
"and accessible so that everyone can know and learn, and also copy and share."
"\n"
"Open participation\n"
"Means that anyone can join or extend the network, respecting its design, its "
"principles and its way of organizing."
msgstr ""

#: 01.en.txt:87
msgid ""
"7c)\n"
"A libre community network is not a free or low cost service for internet "
"connection.\n"
"It is an organized group of people working to guarantee their community's "
"right to communication."
msgstr ""

#: 01.en.txt:90
msgid ""
"8a)\n"
"And, in addition to being a community network, in orde to be a libre network "
"it must meet these four characteristics:"
msgstr ""

#: 01.en.txt:100
msgid ""
"8b)\n"
"Libre use\n"
"It allows unrestricted transit to receive and offer any kind of service and "
"content, so long as it does not affect the good functioning of the network. "
"In other words, the flow of data on the network is unconditional.\n"
"Neutrality\n"
"This characteristic means data traffic is managed in an egalitarian way, "
"without discrimination based on content, platform, application or type of "
"equipment used for access. Data flows within the network are not ranked nor "
"modified arbitrarily.\n"
"Libre interconnection\n"
"This means guaranteeing the interconnection among networks, with a libre, "
"neutral and free of cost flow of data in both directions, reciprocally.\n"
"Libre transit\n"
"Two networks that have a libre transit agreement not only allow data traffic "
"between each other, but also the flow of traffic destined for other networks "
"that they have similar agreements with. The data can therefore cross one "
"libre network to reach another, expanding the reach of the \"network of "
"libre networks.\""
msgstr ""

#: 01.en.txt:105
msgid ""
"9)\n"
"In this illustartion there are two types of interconnection contracts "
"represented:\n"
"- The network of community networks have a contract among themselves as "
"equals for libre transit and for interconnection free of cost, respecting "
"neutrality. Thanks to these contracts, network 1 can communicate with "
"network 3 crossing network 2 without limitations.\n"
"- Networks 2 and 3 have a commercial service to connect with the rest of the "
"internet, via a contractual relationship that is not between peers, but "
"rather provider-consumer. This provider does not share with their clients "
"any aspect of the deployment or configuration of their network."
msgstr ""

#: 01.en.txt:109
msgid ""
"10a)\n"
"Deploying therese libre community networks with a msh topology allows the "
"development of the characteristics mentioned above in a more natural way, "
"given that its basic characteristic is decentralization.\n"
"In this type of mesh network, each wireless node (router and antenna) "
"connects with one or more neighbouring nodes. In this way, the path of data "
"traffic changes automatically when one of the stops functioning. At the same "
"time, it is no longer necessary to have central access points. For these "
"reasons, mesh networks are decentralized and distributed networks."
msgstr ""

#: 01.en.txt:112
msgid ""
"10b)\n"
"A NODE is composed of an antenna, a router and the softwrae that allows "
"connectivity."
msgstr ""

#: 01.en.txt:115
msgid ""
"11a)\n"
"This distributed network design is less expensive because it does not need "
"costly central nodes. The network grows from node to node, extending "
"progressively and keeping the deployment and maintenance costs in pace with "
"network scale."
msgstr ""

#: 01.en.txt:118
msgid ""
"11b)\n"
"When we say that we want to create libre, decentralized community networks, "
"we mean collectively building our little piece of the internet in order to "
"be ourselves more free and communal [or community-spirited]."
msgstr ""

#: 01.en.txt:121
msgid ""
"12a)\n"
"The LibreRouter Project: A community for your network"
msgstr ""

#: 01.en.txt:128
msgid ""
"12b)\n"
"For a long time, libe community networks were built by the collaborative "
"work of people who prgammed and hacked. Together they developed libre "
"software and modified the available hardware, responding to the specific "
"needs of the networks.\n"
"One of the achievements was to change the proprietary software that some "
"commercial household routers came with from the factory.\n"
"This allowed the use of the routers to their full potential, enabling "
"functions that the manufacturers limited according to their market logic. "
"The contribution lowered costs notably for deployment of open, libre, "
"neutral and decentralized networks.\n"
"In August 2016, a regulation emitted by the US state agency FCC (Federal "
"Communitcations Commission) led to the manufacturers blocking the "
"substitution of the software that comes installed and configured from the "
"factory.\n"
"This action made clear that community networks were hostage to arbitrary "
"decisions in which they had little or no capacity to decide or act."
msgstr ""

#: 01.en.txt:132
msgid ""
"13a)\n"
"The LibreRouter project develops hardware, software and documentation "
"focused on the needs of digitally excluded areas of the global south.\n"
"Some notable characteristics include:"
msgstr ""

#: 01.en.txt:139
msgid ""
"13b)\n"
"Hardware\n"
"The router and its antennas are protected by weather-resistant plastic cases."
"\n"
"The board has different connectors available to adapt the node to particular "
"uses. For example, a GPS module.\n"
"The design of the hardware is available for whomever wants to study, modify "
"and reproduce it, since it is libre hardware.\n"
"The LibreRouter comes ready to use with LibreMesh preinstalled."
msgstr ""

#: 01.en.txt:145
msgid ""
"14a)\n"
"Software \n"
"The applications and programs are designed as part of a process in which "
"people without knowledge of networks can learn to configure, map, monitor "
"and troubleshoot the network with ease.\n"
"Simplifies network expansion. New nodes auto-configure based on the "
"information they recieve from existing nodes.\n"
"All software developed by AlterMundi has a libre license, so anyone can use "
"it and adapt it to their needs."
msgstr ""

#: 01.en.txt:151
msgid ""
"14b)\n"
"Documentation\n"
"Our documentation explains the use of the LibreRouter and the applications "
"that come with it.\n"
"On our website docs.altermundi.net all the documentation is available in "
"illustrated and audiovisual form and in multiple languages.\n"
"Anyone can freely use, copy, modify, translate and share our content."
msgstr ""

#: 01.en.txt:154
msgid ""
"15a)\n"
"A network in your community"
msgstr ""

#: 01.en.txt:158
msgid ""
"15b)\n"
"Through our documentation, we share one possible way to organize a community "
"to begin this path of building a libre community network for internet in "
"your communities.\n"
"It is a continous cyclical process of mutual aid among people to carry out "
"the organization of the work and the goals."
msgstr ""

#: 01.en.txt:163
msgid ""
"15c)\n"
"Planning\n"
"Deployment\n"
"Maintenance"
msgstr ""

#: 01.en.txt:166
msgid ""
"15d)\n"
"These cycles of work and organization guide the deployment and maintenance "
"of the network and they continue throughout its existence and development, "
"strengthening and transforming the network. These cycles contribute to the "
"creation of the network as a meeting place and collective identity."
msgstr ""

